Types of Jobs





Chevron in Singapore






Singapore
                    Job Openings



Since 1933, Singapore has played a critical role in Chevron's global operations. The International Products business unit, which covers Chevron's Downstream fuels businesses and joint ventures in Asia Pacific, Africa, Middle East, Pakistan and Europe, is headquartered in Singapore.
It is home to Chevron's Asia-Pacific headquarters for the Manufacturing, Supply and Trading, Marketing, and Lubricants operations. Chevron Upstream has a presence in Singapore through our shipping, global gas and power generation businesses. Chevron Asia Pacific Exploration and Production also has a regional office in Singapore. Other Singapore operations include shipping, global gas and power generation.
The Caltex™ brand, which serves customers in Asia, the Middle East and Africa, is managed from Singapore. Singapore is also Chevron Oronite's regional headquarters for Asia-Pacific and home to one of the largest fuel and lubricant additives manufacturing facility in Asia.

Who We Hire
Where You'll Work
How to Apply
Compensation and Benefits
Career Development Support

Who We Hire

        Chevron values integrity, trust, diversity and ingenuity as a company and in our
        employees. In Singapore, Chevron hires full-time employees with the relevant education
        and experience. We also look for individuals with the following qualities:
    

Have a collaborative work style.
Enjoy a diverse and teamwork-oriented environment.
Are solution-oriented and outcome-driven.


Back to Top

Where You'll Work

        Depending on your role, your journey at Chevron could take you to one or more of
        these locations in Singapore, as well as to other locations around the globe:

Jurong Island — Home to Chevron Oronite's regional headquarters for Asia-Pacific and Singapore manufacturing plant.
Raffles Place — Chevron Downstream Asia Pacific Headquarters is situated at Chevron House.  It is also a regional hub for Chevron Upstream & Gas.
Jalan Buroh — Chevron's fuels terminal and lubricants blending plant.


