Chevron is one of the world's leading energy companies, with approximately 60,000 employees working in countries around the world. We explore, produce and transport crude oil and natural gas; refine, market and distribute fuels and other energy products; manufacture and sell petrochemical products; generate power; and develop future energy resources, including biofuels and geothermal energy.
 
Chevron is accepting online applications for the position of Mobile Solution Product Manager located in San Ramon, California through August 9, 2017 at 11:59 p.m. (Eastern Standard Time).
 
Overview:
 
Primary responsibility of this position is to develop and implement an integrated mobile solution enabling B2C products and programs for fuels retail customers. This role is a member of the Business Technology Innovation team focused on development of solutions based on innovative technologies, which help drive consumer spend and fuel volume sales.
 
Requsition ID#208803
Responsibilities for this position may include but are not limited to:
 

Lead development of a seamlessly integrated mobile solution with a cross-functional team of external providers and internal stakeholders.
Oversee integration points between Mobile Payments Platform Application, Mobile Application (user interface), Point of Sale vendors, payments processors, external partners, and other internal and external systems.
Maintain a roadmap for mobile-based products, project schedules, milestones, and release checklists.
Establish and maintain partnerships with a mobile commerce platform provider and mobile application developer. Ensure adequate product support (features, upgrades, roadmap).
Drive continuous innovation of the mobile commerce platform. Use competitive analysis, research and data to inform the platform strategy. Provide analysis and recommendation for new features, optimizations, and other methods to improve the overall end-user experience.
Engage with cross-functional teams on the evaluation of new payment products and loyalty programs. Act a subject-matter expert in advising stakeholders on how to enable products/programs on the mobile platform.

 
Required qualifications:
 

Bachelor's degree in Information Technology, Software Engineering or other technology fields
A minimum of 5 years of experience in product management of mobile or other digital platform applications
Strong understanding of platform service models, including Platform as a Service (PaaS)
Experience in project management, Agile development methodologies, and ability to manage multiple teams across vendors
Strong analytical skills for making product decisions and rapid product iteration
Strategic thinking and demonstrated proactive problem solving
Experience in leading discussions with business and technology stakeholders, developing use cases and value propositions

 
Preferred qualifications:
 

Master’s degree in Information Technology or Business Administration
Project management certifications
Motivated with desire to continue growth of knowledge in mobile commerce industry
Experience in retail industry
	 

Relocation Options:

Relocation will not be considered.

International Considerations:

Expatriate assignments will not be considered.
 
Chevron regrets that it is unable to sponsor employment Visas or consider individuals on time-limited Visa status for this position.
 
 
Regulatory Disclosure for US Positions:
 
Chevron is an Equal Opportunity / Affirmative Action employer.  Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, disability or protected veteran status, or other status protected by law or regulation.
 
Chevron participates in E-Verify in certain locations as required by law.
 






